offices.name: Döbling
offices.description: Welcome to the Lost and Found Office, your go-to place for reclaiming lost items and reporting found belongings! Nestled in the heart of downtown, our office is located on the second floor of the City Hall Annex, just across from the bustling central park. As you enter, you’ll find a bright and inviting space adorned with colorful posters showcasing items that have been found recently, along with friendly staff ready to assist you. Our office hours are Monday through Friday, from 9 AM to 5 PM. We are committed to helping you reconnect with your lost possessions—whether it’s your favorite pair of sunglasses, a lost umbrella, or a cherished piece of jewelry. To ensure a smooth experience, please bring a form of identification and a brief description of the item you’re looking for. Our staff will guide you through the process of searching our extensive inventory of lost items. For your convenience, there is ample parking available nearby, as well as access to public transportation. We look forward to helping you reunite with your belongings!

faqs.question: What should I do if I lost an item?
faqs.answer: If you've lost an item, please visit our office in person or fill out our online lost item report form. Be sure to provide a detailed description of the item, where and when you last saw it, and your contact information.

faqs.question: How can I report a found item?
faqs.answer: If you have found an item, please bring it to our office or submit a found item report through our website. Include a description of the item, the location where you found it, and your contact information.

faqs.question: What items are commonly found in the Lost and Found?
faqs.answer: Common items include clothing, bags, electronics (like phones and laptops), keys, and personal items (such as wallets or jewelry). However, we receive a wide variety of items, so check back often!

faqs.question: How long do you keep lost items?
faqs.answer: We typically keep lost items for 30 days. After that, unclaimed items may be donated to charity or disposed of, depending on their condition and value.

faqs.question: How will I know if my lost item has been found?
faqs.answer: If your item matches a found report, we will contact you using the information you provided when reporting the loss. Be sure to check your email and phone for updates.

faqs.question: Can I check the Lost and Found inventory online?
faqs.answer: Yes, you can view a list of recently found items on our website. However, please note that not all items may be listed online. It’s best to visit our office if you’re looking for something specific.

faqs.question: What information do I need to provide to claim a lost item which something something something?
faqs.answer: To claim a lost item, please bring a valid ID and provide details about the item (e.g., description, date and location of loss). This will help us verify your ownership.

faqs.question: Is there a fee for retrieving a lost item?
faqs.answer: There is no fee to retrieve your lost item. However, certain items (like electronic devices) may require you to show proof of ownership before they can be returned.

faqs.question: What if I don’t remember where I lost my item?
faqs.answer: If you’re unsure where you lost your item, provide as much information as possible when filing your report. Details like the last time you used the item or places you visited can help us locate it.

faqs.question: Can I report a lost item if I’m not a student/employee?
faqs.answer: Yes, anyone can report a lost item. Please provide your contact information, a description of the item, and any details that can help us identify it.

faqs.question: How to add a new question?
faqs.answer: Wait for our staff to provide the answer
